postcontent:
Hello all brothers/sisters in arms.

Im writing to bring my situation to your attention. Pike County Sheriffs department issued me a citation for "Breach of Peace" for shooting my (legal) guns, during legal (country law) shooting hours. The deputy said its NOT for the guns, its for the noise. Definition of "breach of peace" is in-sighting war, violence, or threatening others. A trumped up charge to suffice my pesky neighbors on speed dial.

I ask that ALL shooters of Pike County Illinois stand with me and tell these out of control ticket writing police officers that enough is enough. They need to do their jobs, NOT fold to whiny neighbors that have the cops on speed dial. We MUST let them know that this kind of behavior from an elected official (Sheriff Petty) will not be tolerated. 

They are supposed to follow the laws just like the citizens. I followed ALL the laws. My shooting has never been excessive, despite what the neighbors say. They are full of the typical liberal lies, and I was ticketed because the cops were tired of them calling in for me shooting. 

I was visited by sheriff's deputies a total of 5 times in a week. 4 times they told me that Im doing nothing wrong, and that Im following ALL the laws. On the fifth visit, they issued the citation.

A citation for "Breach of Peace" was issued to me at my house on Saturday 12-20-14 @ NOON - For shooting trap in my yard (6+ acres). We shot for 45 minutes.

This problem does not stop with me. I've learned that many, many, many people are having the same issues. 

ITS TIME TO END THIS NOW.

Pike County needs your support.

Lets fill the court room and peacefully protest this. If they get away with actually prosecuting this ticket, YOU COULD BE NEXT!

title: For Sale:  sold Chinese Type 53shi Trials Rifle, Very uncommon
location: Minneapolis Metro, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
This is the Chinese produced version of the venerable Mosin-Nagant M44 Carbine.  China called it the Type 53 Carbine and it has been widely exported. 

This specific example was produced in December, 1953 at Plant 296 and is technically a T53 shi (Translated Trails Rifle).  It is in really decent shape for its age and the metal finish is worn to a nice even 10-15% patina.  The stock is dense like walnut and exhibits only a few scuffs and bruises from military service and the surplus importation process.  This is an older import that predates the really hammered ones that are coming into the country now.  Comes with the original sling as shown in the photos.  Rifle is import marked on the receiver, is non matching, and is missing the cleaning rod.

Very uncommon to find a Trails rifle today and would be a welcome addition to any Mosin-Nagant collection.

Cal 7.62x54R with fair bore (dark, some minor pitting noted).

REF number 8652  SALE PENDING
